The paper discusses the resilience analysis of blockchain systems using game theory, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). It also talks about the extension of blockchain from a linear to a non-linear structure for performance improvements, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the trade-off between scalability and finality-duration, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper establishes a formal framework and proves certain results, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
